Package env

Class BlackForestModel

java.lang.Object
env.BlackForestModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
MapModel
public class BlackForestModel extends Object implements MapModel
The `BlackForestModel` class represents the underlying data and logic for the Black Forest simulation. It manages the state of the environment, including agents, resources, and game mechanics. As part of the Model-View-Controller (MVC) pattern, this class serves as the **Model**, encapsulating the core simulation logic and maintaining the game state. It interacts with `BlackForestGameMap` for spatial and environmental data, while notifying the **View** (`BlackForestView`) about updates.
